JOHANNESBURG - ANC Eastern Cape councillor Andile Lungisa will spend his first night in jail on Wednesday. He has been sentenced to two years in prison and denied leave to appeal his conviction. Lungisa was found guilty of assault with intent to cause grievous bodily harm after he smashed a glass jug over the head of Nelson Mandela Bay mayoral committee member Rano Kayser two years ago. WATCH: DA, ANC blame each other for NMB council chaos The court found Lungisa showed no remorse, and would not take responsibility for his actions. eNCA